testabilityexplorer.name: testabilityexplorer

lotus-connections-plugin.title: Lotus Connections plugin
lotus-connections-plugin.excerpt: This plugin posts build results to Lotus Connections.
lotus-connections-plugin.name: lotus-connections-plugin

rvm.title: RVM Plugin
rvm.excerpt: This plugin runs your jobs in the RVM managed ruby+gemset of your choice
rvm.name: rvm

android-emulator.title: Android Emulator Plugin
android-emulator.excerpt: Lets you automatically generate, launch and interact with an Android emulator during a build, with the emulator logs being captured as artifacts.
android-emulator.name: android-emulator

maven-info.title: Maven Info Plugin

description-column-plugin.title: Description Column Plugin

description-column-plugin.name: description-column-plugin

ircbot.name: ircbot

ssh-agent.title: SSH Agent Plugin

nabaztag.title: Nabaztag Plugin

slave-setup.name: slave-setup

jenkins-jira-issue-updater.name: jenkins-jira-issue-updater

openid.excerpt: This plugin lets your Jenkins users login to Jenkins through external OpenID providers, without using password.

emotional-jenkins-plugin.name: emotional-jenkins-plugin

staf.title: STAF - STAX Plugin

staf.name: staf

deploy-websphere.excerpt: This plugin is an extension of the Deploy Plugin. It takes a war/ear file and deploys that to a running remote WebSphere Application Server at the end of a build.
deploy-websphere.name: deploy-websphere

mailcommander.title: Mail Commander Plugin
mailcommander.excerpt: This plugin is provide function that command with e-mail. Write CLI command to e-mail subject and send to pre setting address. Mail Commander recieve e-mail from pre setting address, and read e-mail subject as CLI command, execute it.
mailcommander.name: mailcommander

jenkins-multijob-plugin.name: jenkins-multijob-plugin

xvfb.excerpt: Lets you control Xvfb virtual frame buffer X11 server with each build. It starts Xvfb before the build starts, and stops it with the build. This is very useful if your build requires X11 access, for instance runs tests that require GUI.
xvfb.name: xvfb

svn-revert-plugin.name: svn-revert-plugin
